Reposted from @iamserenaofficial @olgapankova IS a live wedding painter - I cannot believe she made this in I think 5 hours because she left around 11pm (correct me if I'm wrong @olgapankova I highly recommend her professionalism and she sealed the painting so my overexciting big bro/ lil bro Sim who was overjoyed at seeing it didn't mess it up when he just loved it so much. Love is this contagious feeling people get its rooted in creativity and beauty and the artist herself is so patient and devoted to the couple - it's funny she paints on a designer perfume bottle to enhance its value but charges nothing for it at pop ups around the city. She gets paid by Nordstrom or Holt Renfrew to add premium art to a mediocre item cause we all know luxury items just have mark-up. Because rich people are willing to pay for exclusivity but poor people will pay less for a knock off to get the value. I'm poor in money but rich in heart and I never regret it because the laughter in any household poor or rich has the same value - it fills your heart. Bless you @olgapankova you make my heart sing with this painting and it will last years after your 5 hours. It sustains my heart. And Kunal looks perfect he even did the sign for it an OKAY in the Western word. Or a period. Or the peacock feathers of Krishna. ❤️ She works with your budget she has much larger options and a few smaller ones. Please message her because she gets booked up fast. 

#painting #krishnapeacockfeathers #artislife #indianweddings #bridalasia #wedluxe @bridalasia @wedluxetoronto
